name: Sara Phillips - new york without me

metadata.description:
written by Sara Phillips.
produced by Mike Daley and Sara Phillips. 


you see my face in everyone on Bowery
and the coffee shop we loved just pours for one
Broadway's just a busy street without me
and the hurt walks you home when the party's done

cause your mother still asks about me
and your dad calls every girl my name
your friends still ask about me
must be hard having no one else to blame 

are you sleeping soundly 
in New York without me?
do you search the streets at night looking for more?
are you sleeping soundly
in New York without me?
hope you're finding what it is you're looking for 

the winter's colder than it's ever been
and Christmas comes without a parade
the summer just reminds you of my skin
and the memories you wish you could erase

cause your mother still asks about me
and your dad calls every girl my name
your friends still ask about me
and things will never be the same

are you sleeping soundly 
in New York without me?
do you search the streets at night looking for more?
are you sleeping soundly
in New York without me?
hope you're finding what it is you're looking for 

how do you sleep?
how do you sleep?
how do you sleep?
how do you sleep?
how do you sleep?
how do you sleep?
hope you're finding what it is you're looking for.



10% of this mint will be going to a community member of ours in need. Thank you for your support!
